  "body": "<!-- Have you done the following? -->\r\n<!--   * read the Code of Conduct? By filing an Issue, you are expected to -->  \r\n<!--     comply with it, including treating everyone with respect: -->\r\n<!--     https://github.com/PegasysEng/teku/blob/master/CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md -->\r\n<!--   * Reproduced the issue in the latest version of the software -->\r\n<!--   * Read the debugging wiki: https://github.com/PegasysEng/teku/wiki/debugging -->\r\n<!--   * Duplicate Issue check:  https://github.com/search?q=+is%3Aissue+repo%3APegasysEng/Teku -->\r\n<!-- Note:  Not all sections will apply to all issue types. -->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWhen validating a new block or processing it on block transition the following method is used to validate bolck slashings: https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/blob/fd7ef91e11b6e6bb8992bc5b8354b3406609147c/ethereum/core/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/teku/core/BlockProcessorUtil.java#L260\r\n\r\nThis method looks less reliable than `ProposerSlashingValidator`, e.g. it doesn't check the slashing proposer index explicitly at least. \r\n\r\nWould be good to use `ProposerSlashingValidator` to validate blocks slashings \r\n\r\nSee the comment for original context: https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/pull/3314#discussion_r530667450\r\n\r\nThe same issue with `VoluntartyExits`: https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/pull/3314#discussion_r530667971",
